article.headline: Oregon 83, N.C. State 78
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Cathrine Kraayeveld scored 18 points and
Andrea Bills added 17 to lead No. 24 Oregon past North Carolina
State 83-78 on Saturday night in the Oregon Classic.

Kedzie Gunderson and Kayla Steen both scored 11 points for the
Ducks (5-0), off to their best start since going 6-0 in the 1999-00
season. Kraayeveld also had eight rebounds and Corrie Mizusawa
added 10 assists, her third game this season with 10 or more.

Kaayla Chones scored 25 points for the Wolfpack (2-2) before
fouling out with 1:27 left in the game. Keisha Brown added 15.

The score was tied 69-all with 4:25 to play, but a 3-pointer by
Gunderson gave the Ducks the lead and sparked a 13-4 run that
sealed the victory. Brandi Davis added a 3-pointer and made two
free throws during the spurt.

It was a tightly played first half and the game was tied at 34
at the break.

Chones scored 10 of her points before halftime, but also picked
up three fouls. She was called for her fourth 2:49 into the second
half and was forced to sit for more than six minutes.

During Chone's time on the bench, the Wolfpack unraveled, as
Oregon, up 40-39, went on a 20-8 run to take a 60-47 lead before
Chones re-entered with 10:57 left.

Back-to-back baskets by Bills built the Ducks lead to 64-47
before N.C. State started to chip away, finally tying the game on a
rebound basket by Brown to cap a 22-5 run by the Wolfpack. Chones
scored 12 of those points.
